    <h1>Store specials</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Do you want to highlight certain items in your online store? For example, do you want to display a list of new products, special offers or best sellers directly on the homepage? Then configure store specials in plentymarkets and feature select items in your store!</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Ceres vs. Callisto store</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The procedure varies depending on whether you use a newer Ceres store or an older Callisto store. Both procedures are described on this page.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Store specials in Ceres</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In Ceres, store specials are created with the help of <em>tags</em>. There are three steps to the process:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/welcome/general-functions/tags">Create the tags</a> that you want to use for your items, e.g. "Best seller”.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/managing-items#150">Link your variations to the tags</a>. For example, give all of your best selling items the “Best seller” tag.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/online-store/setting-up-ceres#110">Create an item list</a> to display the tagged items in your online store. Don’t forget to specify the ID for your “Best seller” tag.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="200">2. Store specials in Callisto</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Store specials are <em>less flexible</em> in Callisto than they are in Ceres.</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Callisto only allows you to highlight entire items in the online store. Ceres allows you to feature individual variations.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Callisto only allows you to call an item a “Special offer”, “New item” or “Top item”. Ceres allows you to think up your own names.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="300">2.1. Adding items to the store special</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>First, decide which items should be included in the store special.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adding items to the store special:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/introduction/search#100">Search for</a> and open the item that should be included in the store special.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Global</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Find the <strong>Online store</strong> area. Use the <strong>Store special</strong> drop-down list to specify whether you want to call this item a special offer, a new item or a top item.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Other ways to add items</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The instructions above explain how to manually add items to a store special. However, you could also use the group function if you want to <a href="/en/item/managing-items#155">add several items at the same time</a>. Or you could use the procedure manager if you want to <a href="/en/item/online-store/store-specials#400">automatically add items to the store special</a>, e.g. when the price drops.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="400">2.1.1. Automatically adding items to the store special</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use the procedure manager to automatically link items with store specials.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up the procedure manager:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Item » Procedures</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>New procedure</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the procedure <strong>Link items to an online store special</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Configure the settings for the procedure manager. Note <a href="#table-link-store-actions">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
